!!!
html(lang="en")
	head
		meta(charset="utf-8")
		meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0")
		meta(name="description", content="")
		meta(name="author", content="")
		title Webpages for Humans
		link(rel='stylesheet', href='/bootstrap-ui/css/bootstrap.css')
	body
		.container
			.hero-unit
				h1 Web Pages for Humans		
			ul.nav.nav-tabs
				li.active: a(href="#about", data-toggle="tab") About
				li: a(href="#create", data-toggle="tab") Create
				li: a(href="#list", data-toggle="tab") Gallery
		#content.container
			.tab-content
				#about.tab-pane.active
					.row
						.span4
							h1 What is this?
							p 
								| Web Pages for Humans is part of 
								a(href="http://danm.ucsc.edu/~jesse") jesse fulton
								| 's MFA thesis at the 
								a(href="http://danm.ucsc.edu/") Digital Arts + New Media program at UC Santa Cruz
								| .
							p
								| Web Pages for Humans is a web application which creates a version of the Internet which is only readable by humans. Screen-scraping technology is used to generate images of web pages which are then processed by OCR software to find machine-readable text on the page. This text is then manipulated and distorted within the image using CAPTCHA algorithms to create a machine-unreadable version of that web page.
						.span4
							h1 CAPTCHA-fy?
							p
								| What is a captcha? You know, 
								a(href="#captcha-image", data-toggle="modal") like this
							#captcha-image.modal.fade
								.modal-header
									a.close(data-dismiss="modal") x
									h3 Sample CAPTCHA
								.modal-body(style="text-align:center;")
									img(src="/images/captcha-example.png")
							p
								| Google's reCAPTCHA project “digitizes” books, newspapers, and documents by exploiting human labour to decipher words which OCR algorithms are unable of “understanding.” These cultural artifacts are thus transformed into machine-readable computer files. Web Pages for Humans flips this model around, taking machine-generated, machine-readable documents and manipulating them with the CAPTCHA distortion algorithms to ensure that computers can no longer read their own content.
						.span4
							h1 CAPTCHA-why?
							p
								| Why is this important?
							
				#create.tab-pane
					h1 Create
					.form
						p Enter a URL below to CAPTCHA-fy that page
						p: input(type="text", name="generateUrl", id="generateUrl")
						p: a.btn.btn-primary(id="doGenerate", href="#") Generate!
				#list.tab-pane
					h1 Screenshots
					.row
						- if (screenshots.length > 0)
							ul.thumbnails
								- each screen in screenshots
										li.span3.offset1
											a(href="/#{screen.url}", style="height:180px;display:block;overflow:hidden")
												img(src="/#{screen.url}", width="260px")
											h5 #{screen.title}
												a(href="#{screen.url}") #{screen.url}
			

			script(type="text/javascript", src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js")
			script(type="text/javascript", src="/bootstrap-ui/js/jquery.js")
			script(type='text/javascript', src='/bootstrap-ui/js/bootstrap-transition.js')
			script(type='text/javascript', src='/bootstrap-ui/js/bootstrap-tab.js')
			script(type='text/javascript', src='/bootstrap-ui/js/bootstrap-modal.js')
			script(type="text/javascript")
				//$('#captcha-image').modal({"show":false})
				var doGenerate = function() {
					var url = document.getElementById("generateUrl").value;
					window.location = "/" + url;
				}

				$("#doGenerate").on('click', doGenerate);
				$("#generateUrl").on('keypress', function(event) {
					if (event.which == 13) {
						$("#doGenerate").click();
						//doGenerate();
					}
				});